// Package patterns implements the generalization layer of the learning
// subsystem: when a user has taught the CLI to map two or more
// structurally-similar queries to two or more structurally-similar
// resources, this package extracts a template (a "pattern") from the
// group and applies it to substitute new entities at recall time.
//
// # The story this package tells
//
// A user teaches two queries against two resources whose IDs differ
// by an entity slot. Extract walks search_learnings, groups by
// structural signature, finds the entity_kind whose lookups reproduce
// every member's resource ID under one shared template, and writes
// the result to search_patterns. On a future recall whose entity
// wasn't directly taught, Apply substitutes via lookups.Lookup,
// verifies the candidate exists in the resources table, and returns
// a Hit with source="pattern".
//
// # Lineage
//
// This package generalizes a "recipes" package first shipped in
// prediction-goat-pp-cli. The Printing Press port renames recipes ->
// patterns (and Recipe -> Pattern, search_recipes -> search_patterns)
// so the same generator template can ship into CLIs whose domain
// vocabulary already uses "recipes" for its own purpose (food, cooking,
// etc.). The substitution-strategy taxonomy and the binding-search
// algorithm are unchanged. See
// docs/plans/2026-05-23-002-feat-generator-wide-self-learning-cli-plan.md
// for the full design rationale.
//
// # Schema adaptation
//
// The v3 generator schema stores patterns as a flat
// (template TEXT, entity_kind TEXT, confidence INTEGER, source TEXT,
//
//	created_at) row with PK (template, entity_kind). The Pattern struct
//
// here carries a richer shape (query template + resource template +
// resource_type + venue + strategy + examples); we encode that bundle
// as a JSON envelope in the `template` column so the package surface
// stays expressive without changing the schema.
